        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Elizabeth Port. New Jersey</placeName></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>19<hi rend="sup">th</hi> November 1851</date></p>
			<p><addressee>Reverend Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir&#33;</p>
			<p>I have the pleasure to<lb/> acknowledge receipt of your valued favor&#59; and should<lb/> have answered same but had not time to do so ere<lb/> this. I delivered your letter to <persName>Mr. A D. Haar</persName>. I<lb/> truly thank you for your kind expressions&#44; I also<lb/> note the prospectus&#44; and have informed those few&#8212;<lb/>who are living at this port&#44; a Gentleman has requeste&#61;<lb/>&#61;ed me to inquire the prices of the sett&#39;s of books you<lb/> have at present&#44; say with name &#38;c complete. I<lb/> enclose you an Obituary which I shall feel <sic>infinate<lb/>&#44;&#44;ly</sic> obliged if you would give it publication in<lb/> your valuable periodical. I also enclose you fifty<lb/> cents for the two <add>&#63;</add> with many thanks.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">I am Dear Sir</p>
          <p rend="indent(3)">Your Obt Sevt &#38; friend</p>
          <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Benjamin Lindo</persName></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><addressee>Reverend Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName><hi rend="underline">Philadelphia</hi></placeName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p rend="align(center)"><sic><hi rend="underline">Obitury</hi></sic></p>
			<p>Died at <placeName>Elizabeth Port. New Jersey</placeName> on <date>22d<lb/> Hisvan 5612</date> corresponding with the <date>17<hi rend="sup">th</hi> November<lb/> 1851</date>. <persName>David Bair</persName>&#44; Son of <persName>Mr. Abraham Bair</persName><lb/> and Grand Son of <persName>Mr David Haar</persName>&#44; aged<lb/> One year and nine months&#44; his <sic>corpes</sic> was<lb/> taken to <placeName>Williams Burg</placeName> and there entered<lb/> in the <sic>Portagues</sic> new <sic>Buriel</sic> ground&#44; he was<lb/> a fine and sensible child&#44; peace be to his<lb/> departed soul &#45; &#45; &#45; <persName role="author"><hi rend="underline">Benjamin Lindo</hi></persName></p>
          
        </body>
